---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Terms of Use | PDFTwin"
  description="Terms for using PDFTwin's business file conversion tools and workspace."
>
  <article class="legal-page">
    <h1>Terms of Use</h1>
    <p class="legal-updated">Last updated: July 2026</p>

    <section>
      <h2>Service description</h2>
      <p>
        PDFTwin provides online tools to convert, organize, compare, and protect business
        documents. Features and limits may change as the product evolves.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Acceptable use</h2>
      <p>You agree not to use PDFTwin to:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Upload unlawful, harmful, or infringing content</li>
        <li>Attempt to disrupt, reverse engineer, or overload the service</li>
        <li>Circumvent plan limits or security controls</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Your content</h2>
      <p>
        You retain ownership of the files you upload. You are responsible for ensuring you have
        the right to process and download the documents you submit.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Plans and billing</h2>
      <p>
        Free and Pro plans may offer different file-size limits and features. Paid subscriptions,
        when enabled, are billed through PayPal according to the plan selected at checkout.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Disclaimer</h2>
      <p>
        PDFTwin is provided on an &ldquo;as is&rdquo; basis. Conversion quality can vary by source
        file complexity. Review outputs before sending them to clients or regulators.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Changes</h2>
      <p>
        We may update these terms or the service from time to time. Continued use of PDFTwin
        after changes are posted constitutes acceptance of the revised terms.
      </p>
    </section>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
